<HEAD>U.S. To Help Arrange Loan for Debt-Troubled Argentina</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The <ORGANIZATION> Treasury </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> said Thursday it is working with debt-troubled <LOCATION> Argentina </LOCATION> to arrange a short-term loan of up to $ 500 million from the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> and other creditor nations. The so-called `` bridge'' loan would allow <LOCATION> Argentina </LOCATION> to meet interest payments on its $ 56 billion foreign debt while it negotiates with the <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Monetary </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Fund </ORGANIZATION> and the <ORGANIZATION> World </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION>. But, according to a department statement, funds from the short-term loan, will not become available until <LOCATION> Argentina </LOCATION> `` meets the requirements ... under the <ORGANIZATION> World </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION>'s ... lending program.'' <LOCATION> Argentina </LOCATION>, which is more than 90 days past due on more than $ 300 million in payments, has said it can not afford to make its overdue interest payments. Recently, the nation has taken measures to cut its budget deficit and check its inflation, running about 20 percent a month. This week, it declared a three-day bank holiday and devalued its currency. `` The <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>' willingness to participate in this effort reflects support for <LOCATION> Argentina </LOCATION>'s economic reform efforts and the determination of the government of <LOCATION> Argentina </LOCATION> to address its international financial relations in a constructive manner,'' the <ORGANIZATION> Treasury </ORGANIZATION> statement said. It said the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> is working with other creditor governments through the <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> for </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Set